<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-195-139 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 512 876</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  March 25 1991 n413 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>VARs face competition from aggressive users: resellers shiftstrategy to keep pace. (value-added resellers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Doyle, T.C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Time Inc joined the ranks oftechnology-consumers-turned-solutions-providers when it announcedit would enter the electronic-publishing-solutions market.andP;  Anumber of companies have decided to market internally developedsolutions to consumers in order to recover research anddevelopment costs.andP;  Some of these end-user-VARs have been givenofficial status by vendors.andP;  This promises to alter an alreadycompetitive VAR channel.andP;  Resellers in many diverse niche marketsare seeing cases where users convert from technology consumers tosolutions marketers.andP;  The list includes Westinghouse, GeneralElectric and Mellon Bank.andP;  The trend is common enough that manyresellers are taking particular notice.andP;  They find comfort in thefact that not all such conversions are successful.andP;  It does forceresellers to reevaluate their businesses.andP;  They complain whenvendors award reseller authorizations to users but the complaintshave not slowed the trend.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Time Inc. (Diversification).andO;Ticker:    TL.andO;Topic:     Value-Added ResellersComputer RetailingDiversified CompaniesUser RelationsMarketing StrategyMarket Entry.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>